      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "WESTBOUND (6) missed fresh before bolting in over 1400m last time out, putting 2.1L on his rivals as the odds-on favourite. Out to 1800m now, but that doesn't look an issue with the way he's closed off over a mile previously. Likely to get back in the run, but watch for him launching late. FIFTH ESSENCE (3) sat handy but couldn't get the job done here last time out when 1.5L off the winner. He rates highly off that effort though and he has the speed to roll across from a sticky gate. Nottle's claim sees him drop plenty of weight and he can put his best foot forward. SIMPLY THINKIN' (2) flew home last time out when getting back over 1600m and she steps up to 1800m now. Wouldn't surprise to sit closer this time around with CJP remaining in the saddle. Can feature. ODINAKA (1) is hard to knock on recent form and has to be included. BLACK FOR CASH (4) can bounce back after a 2.7L defeat most recently.",
